==English==
===Adjective===
'''gelid'''
#Very cold
#Icy or frosty

"a man of gelid reserve" -- New Yorker

"In the worst of summer the tower remained cool, yet the air seemed feverish and gelid when sisters of different Ajahs came too close." ''Knife of Dreams'' Robert Jordan

===Etymology===
From the Latin [[gelidus]].

